A vintage 1950s pharmaceutical advertisement style illustration showing a retro doctor in a white coat examining a large butterfly emerging from a cocoon, with swirling transformation imagery surrounding them. The butterfly's wings display intricate circuit board patterns blending with organic natural textures. The doctor holds an old-fashioned magnifying glass, peering with exaggerated curiosity and slight apprehension at the metamorphosis. Muted cream, teal, and coral color palette typical of mid-century medical posters. Halftone dot texture overlay throughout. The scene conveys both the anxiety and wonder of technological change and evolution.
